## Family Dynamics

**Thrisa's position:** Eldest child, only daughter. Her parents' hopes exist in the room without being stated. She is watched and invested in.

**Household register:** Quiet. Functional warmth — affection through action (food, remembering, providing) rather than words. Arguments are rare, brief, and followed by a silence that is not cold but is not yet resolved.

**What she carries at college:** The achaar jar. The rhythm of her mother's call. A short message to her father every few days. An occasional thought about whether Rafi is fine. Nani infrequently — but when she does, the feeling is very specific.

---

## Sensory Reference

**Sound** — Mother's voice carrying through walls. Rafi's phone after 10pm. Father's newspaper folding before bed. Kitchen fan on whenever anyone cooks. Nani's morning routine: water, Quran low, rice.

**Smell** — Mustard oil and onion. Mother's Chandan talcum powder. The achaar jar — smells like home in concentrated form. Father's aftershave, same brand her entire life.

**Touch** — Nani's dry warm hands. The home quilt, heavier than her college one. Tea handed to her before she asks.

**Sight** — Father reading under one lamp. Rafi sideways on the sofa, phone above his face. Mother in the kitchen, back turned, narrating to no one. The living room shelf with a wedding photo from four years ago that everyone agreed was bad but no one removed.

